.TH CLA_get_value_positional 3
.SH NAME
CLA_get_value_positional \- Get the value associated with a positional command line argument
.SH LIBRARY
cla library (\fIlibcla\fR, \fI\-lcla\fR)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include \[dq]cla/cla.h\[dq]
.br
\fBconst char * CLA_get_value_positional (const struct cla * \fIself\fR\fB,
                                       int \fIipos\fR\fB);
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B CLA_get_value_positional
gets the value associated with a registered positional command line argument at index \fIipos\fR,
using the information from \fIself\fR. Indexing is 0-based and starts at the first
positional argument.
.I self
can be constructed using
\fBCLA_create\fR.
Registering the number of positional arguments can be done with
\fBCLA_add_positionals\fR.
.SH RETURN VALUE
A pointer to the positional argument at index \fIipos\fR. Any subsequent parsing is left to the user.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBCLA\fR(3), \fBCLA_add_positionals\fR(3), \fBCLA_create\fR(3)
